article.headline: Stony Brook 79, Hartford 73
article.story: HARTFORD, Conn. -- Bryan Dougher scored nine consecutive points in overtime to lift Stony Brook to a 79-73 comeback win over Hartford on Wednesday night, sweeping the season series. The Seawolves (12-16, 7-8 America East Conference), who shot a season-high 50 percent (27 of 54), overcame a 10-point deficit with 6:05 left in regulation. Leonard Hayes hit a 3-pointer to tie it at 63 with 6 seconds on the clock. The Hawks (9-19, 6-9) who lost to Stony Brook 69-35 on Jan. 29, pulled ahead 67-64 in overtime. After Danny Carter's free throw made it 67-65, Dougher scored on a 3-pointer, a jumper, a layup and two free throws to give Stony Brook a 74-67 lead, the 17th lead change of the game, with 46 seconds left. Hartford got to 76-73 with 26 seconds left, then the Seawolves hit 3 of 4 free throws to seal the win. Joe Zeglinski had 24 points, hitting seven of the Hawks' 15 3-pointers.
